---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About | The Startup at the End of the Universe">
  <SEO
    slot="head"
    title="About | The Startup at the End of the Universe"
    description="What is this blog, why does it exist, and why is it transmitting from the end of spacetime? All excellent questions. Read on."
  />

  <div class="about-content">
    <section>
      <h1>// About This Blog</h1>
      <p>
        You have somehow stumbled upon a blog that is being broadcast from the
        final remaining server in the universe. The server is located just past
        the last Tesco, orbiting a dying star that the locals have named "Keith."
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>The Startup at the End of the Universe</strong> is a blog about
        technology, small business, and the quiet absurdity of trying to build
        something useful while the economy rearranges itself around you. It is
        written in the tradition of noticing things and then writing them down,
        which is the oldest and least profitable form of content creation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="construction-notice">
      *** THIS PAGE IS UNDER CONSTRUCTION ***<br />
      It has been under construction since before the beginning of time.<br />
      It will remain under construction until after the end of it.
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>// What Sort of Things Will I Find Here?</h2>
      <p>
        Excellent question. The honest answer is: whatever the author felt like
        writing about at the time. Topics may include but are not limited to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Technology and its many amusing failures</li>
        <li>The strange customs of people who build things on the internet</li>
        <li>Small business in an economy that would prefer you didn't</li>
        <li>Observations that seemed very clever at 2 AM</li>
        <li>Whatever else fits the vibe</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If you're looking for a serious blog with a clear editorial mission
        and a content calendar, you may wish to look elsewhere. Might we suggest
        the rest of the internet?
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>// About the Author</h2>
      <p>
        This blog is written by Stephen Sciortino, a small-business owner who
        spends most of his time building things with computers and the rest of it
        wondering why. He lives and works at what appears to be the end of one
        economic era and the beginning of another, which is an interesting place
        to be if you don't think about it too hard.
      </p>
      <p>
        Complaints may be submitted in writing to the void.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="ascii-divider">=-=~=-=~=-=~=-=~=-=~=-=~=-=~=-=~=-=~=-=</div>

    <div class="guestbook-prompt">
      Sign our <a href="#">guestbook</a>! (Just kidding. Or are we?)
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
